<li id="cite_note-71"><b><a href="#cite_ref-71" title="">^</a></b> The first attacks may have been launched prematurely due to confusion over a changeover in the calendar date by Vietcong units. Hanoi had arbitrarily forwarded the date of the holiday in order to allow its citizens respite from the retaliatory airstrikes that were sure to follow the offensive. Whether this was connected to the mixup over the launch date is unknown. All eight of the attacks were controlled by the North Vietnamese headquarters of Military Region 5.</li>
